<div xmlns:java="http://xml.apache.org/xslt/java" id="centre_col"><!-- begin original content --><h1>ESSUM31350 - General requirements
for approval: Scaling down</h1>
<br>
<p>The following successive steps are acceptable in scaling down
applications for options:</p>
<br>
<ol type="1" start="1">
<li>each election for the maximum bonus to be included in the
repayment under the savings contract, shall be deemed to be an
election for only the standard bonus to be included.
<br>
<br>
</li>
<li>each election for any bonus to be included shall be deemed to
be an election for no bonus to be included.
<br>
<br>
</li>
<li>each application for a five year contract shall be deemed to be
an application for a three year contract.
<br>
<br>
</li>
<li>the excess over the minimum (&pound;5-&pound;10) monthly savings
contribution chosen by each applicant shall be reduced pro rata.
<br>
<br>
</li>
<li>applications will be selected by lot, each based on a monthly
savings contribution of the minimum (&pound;5-&pound;10) and the
inclusion of no bonus in the repayment under the savings contract.
<br>
<br>
</li>
</ol>
<p>A scheme which provides that only applications above a fixed

limit (specified in the scheme) may be scaled down is acceptable

provided that the specified limit can be shown to satisfy the

similar terms requirements. Scheme advisors may accept that a limit

of &pound;50 or less does so, without making further enquiries.

<br>
<br> Other scaling down arrangements may be acceptable as

satisfying the "similar terms" requirements, and should be examined

on their own merits.

<br>
<br> Where a scheme&rsquo;s invitation process provides scope for

employees to make multiple applications, see 

<a href="ESSUM34520.htm">ESSUM34520</a>, an employee&rsquo;s

various applications should be aggregated before any scaling down

is applied to them.

<br>
<br> Taking into account, when scaling down, how much an

applicant is already saving under existing savings contracts (so as

to favour new savers or current low savers) does not satisfy the

similar terms requirements of paragraph 7. The similar terms

requirements relate to "rights to be obtained" and are not

concerned with the size of existing options held. Nor is a

participant's level of existing savings a similar factor to

remuneration or length of service. Companies which wish to favour

new or low savers should bear this in mind when setting the

scheme's maximum permitted aggregate monthly savings limit under

paragraph 25 Schedule 3, see 

<a href="ESSUM34510.htm">ESSUM34510</a>.

<br>
<br> Once an agreed scaling down procedure provided for in the

scheme rules has been commenced, it cannot be altered for the

tranche of options to which the applications relate. If the company

wishes to apply a different basis for scaling down provided for in

the scheme rules (or an amendment to the scheme rules if

necessary), another invitation process must be commenced so that

the options granted as a result of it are granted in accordance

with the provisions of the approved scheme.</p>
<br>
